    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Process used for holograms captured and processed at up to 40 frames per second, allowing video-rate holographic imaging. Potential uses for this technology include holographic video display for examination of objects, medical imaging, 3-D video conferencing, and other purposes.</Note_Text>
